{
  "stem": "17526.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But due to the effect that Bendin or Bedzin was such a densely populated-- thickly populated Jewish-- by Jewish people, this school was as Jewish school, not by design but it just happened so that most of the citizens in this town were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The religious school was the Agudah Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Agudah, A-G-U-D-A-H-- Agudah Israel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And again, that school was highly recognized as a very intenstive school of-- of religious studies.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How long?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About I would say-- about six years in the Agudah and about four years in the-- three or four years in the public school, from which I graduated.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My home life before the war was rather interesting in a way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all belonged to-- every youngster, almost everyone I knew, and there was hardly anybody that did not belong to some kind of organization, mostly Zionist organizations, from the extreme right to the extreme left.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Naturally, I belonged to the religious Zionist organizations, where others went to the other extreme.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But each youngster felt a sense of you have to belong, otherwise you were just nobody.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You were feeling a sense of identity, you were part of a movement, that you were building your hopes for the future.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the future, naturally, was to someday immigrate to Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The official language in the school was nationalist Polish and in the street people were speaking Polish, but at home, Yiddish was the mother tongue, or the [YIDDISH] as they would say in the slang Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yiddish was the language that we were born and raised.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
